.TH agecalc 1 "November 2025" "Age Calculator"
.SH NAME
agecalc \- calculate your age from birthdate
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B agecalc
\fB\-b\fR YYYY-MM-DD [\fB-y\fR|\fB-d\fR|\fB-u\fR|\fB-f\fR|\fB-h\fR|\fB-v\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
agecalc is a command line utility that calculates your age from your birthdate and provides different output formats such as age in years, total days lived, and days until your next birthday.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-b\fR YYYY-MM-DD
Specify your birthdate in Year-Month-Day format. (Required)
.TP
\fB-y\fR
Show only the age in years.
.TP
\fB-d\fR
Show only the total number of days lived.
.TP
\fB-u\fR
Show the number of days remaining until the next birthday.
.TP
\fB-f\fR
Show full information: age in years, months, days, total days lived, and days until next birthday.
.TP
\fB-h\fR
Display help information and exit.
.TP
\fB-v\fR
Display version information and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Calculate age with full information:
.B agecalc -b 2000-11-24 -f
.TP
Show only years:
.B agecalc -b 2000-11-24 -y
.TP
Check days lived:
.B agecalc -b 2000-11-24 -d
.TP
Days until next birthday:
.B agecalc -b 2000-11-24 -u
